Module io.netty5.handler
Package io.netty5.handler.ssl

Class PemPrivateKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.netty5.buffer.api.BufferHolder<PemPrivateKey>
      • io.netty5.handler.ssl.PemPrivateKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Resource<PemPrivateKey>, Serializable, AutoCloseable, Key, PrivateKey, Destroyable
    public final class PemPrivateKey
extends BufferHolder<PemPrivateKey>
implements PrivateKey
    This is a special purpose implementation of a PrivateKey which allows the user to pass PEM/PKCS#8 encoded key material straight into OpenSslContext without having to parse and re-encode bytes in Java land.

    All methods other than what's implemented in PemEncoded and Destroyable throw UnsupportedOperationExceptions.

    See Also:
    PemEncoded, OpenSslContext, valueOf(byte[]), valueOf(Buffer), Serialized Form
